Potential questions to consider exploring:

  • Does rating vary by neighborhood, room type, or both?
  • How is price related to other variables?
  • Where are rentals located?
  • Which neighborhood has the highest reviews?
  • Is availability related to price?
  • Is room type related neighborhood?
  • Is length of stay related to borough?
# some variable modification

nyc_airbnb = 
  nyc_airbnb %>% 
  mutate(
    stars = review_scores_location / 2
  ) %>% 
  rename(borough = neighbourhood_group)

Counting things:

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  count(room_type, borough) %>% 
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = room_type,
    values_from = n

# price and room type

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = stars, y = price)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_grid(. ~ room_type) +
  theme_minimal()
## Warning: Removed 10037 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

# price and neighborhood

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  group_by(borough) %>% 
  summarize(mean_price = mean(price, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = borough,
    values_from = mean_price
  )
## # A tibble: 1 × 5
##   Bronx Brooklyn Manhattan Queens `Staten Island`
##   <dbl>    <dbl>     <dbl>  <dbl>           <dbl>
## 1  82.8     120.      180.   94.7            128.
# looking closer at brooklyn

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(borough == "Brooklyn") %>% 
  group_by(neighbourhood) %>% 
  summarize(mean_price = mean(price, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
  arrange(desc(mean_price)) %>% 
  view()

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(borough == "Brooklyn") %>% 
  count(neighbourhood) %>% 
  arrange(desc(n)) %>% 
  view()

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(
    borough == "Brooklyn",
    price <= 1000
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    neighbourhood = fct_reorder(neighbourhood, price)
  ) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = neighbourhood, y = price)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  coord_flip() +
  facet_grid(. ~ room_type)

# price vs. location

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  group_by(borough) %>% 
  summarize(mean_price = mean(price, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = borough,
    values_from = mean_price
  )

# this is cool

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(price > 500) %>% 
  slice_sample(n = 5000) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = lat, y = long, color = price)) + 
  geom_point(alpha = .3)

pal = colorNumeric("viridis", NULL)
nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(price < 500) %>% 
  sample_n(1000) %>% 
  mutate(
    label = str_c("<b>Stars: ", stars, "</b><br>Price: ", price, sep = "")
  ) %>% 
  leaflet() %>% 
  addProviderTiles(providers$CartoDB.Positron) %>% 
  addCircleMarkers(~lat, ~long, radius = 1, popup = ~ label, color = ~pal(price))
